nodes.text: Dynia Reekeene was a human female fighter in the Resistance. She was the daughter of two Rebel Alliance commanders who had led a cell in the Fakir sector, and joined the Resistance in honor of her parents.

Dynia Reekeene first appeared in Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker, and was first identified in the accompanying visual dictionary. She shares her last name with Star Wars Legends characters Lens and Mikka Reekeene, who were Rebel Alliance commanders who led a campaign in the Fakir sector.
